Operatives of the Ogun State Police Command have arrested five men have been arrested for allegedly snatching a car in Iperu, Ikenne Local Government Area. According to the Police, the suspects namely Moruf Abidogun, Afees Adesina, Fisayo Aliu, Usman Adeyemi, and Dauda Lekan belong to a robbery gang terrorizing Iperu, Sagamu, and Ode Remo axis of the state. They were reportedly arrested following a distress call received by the DPO of Iperu Division, SP Waheed Oni. SP Oni had been told that the hoodlums were sighted along Ogere road, dispossessing people of their belongings. Upon the distress call, the DPO was said to have quickly mobilized his men, in collaboration with the Area Command’s anti-robbery team in Sagamu and men of the Ogere patrol team to the scene. The State police spokesman, Abimbola Oyeyemi, said, “On sighting the policemen, the hoodlums who have already snatched a Toyota Corolla car with registration number, GGE 733 FL, took to their heels, but they were hotly chased by the policemen and five of them were apprehended”. According to Oyeyemi, a preliminary investigation has revealed that the gang has its base in Lagos State but members usually visit Iperu to rob, because one of them resides in the town.